      • bigDecimalFromString

        public static BigDecimal bigDecimalFromString(String string,
                                              int firstSpot)
        Takes a string and pulls out a substring representing a BigDecimal starting at designated index until hits next non-Digit, non-period, non-slash, or non-negative sign char. Converts the string to an actual BigDecimal. If the BigDecimal string contains 2 BigDecimal substrings with a '/' between them, all together representing a rational as a fraction, divides the rationals to form one rational value. Examples: bigDecimalFromString("1234", 0) returns 1234 bigDecimalFromString("1234", 2) returns 34 bigDecimalFromString("abs1234.98mhm", 3) returns 1234.98 bigDecimalFromString("abs-1234.98mhm", 3) returns -1234.98 bigDecimalFromString("abs-12/2mhm", 3) returns -6.0000000000
        Parameters:
        string - String holding BigDecimal
        firstSpot - First index of char at beginning of BigDecimal
        Returns:
        BigDecimal BigDecimal from string. If string contains BigDecimal/BigDecimal, returns BigDecimal after dividing the 2 values

      • bigDecimalLengthFromString

        public static int bigDecimalLengthFromString(String string,
                                             int firstSpot)
        Gets the length of a substring representing a BigDecimal in a String Examples: bigDecimalLengthFromString("1234", 0) returns 4 bigDecimalLengthFromString("1234", 2) returns 2 bigDecimalLengthFromString("abs1234.98mhm", 3) returns 7 bigDecimalLengthFromString("abs-1234.98mhm", 3) returns 8 bigDecimalLengthFromString("abs-12/2mhm", 3) returns 5
        Parameters:
        string - String getting BigDecimal from
        firstSpot - First index of char at beginning of BigDecimal
        Returns:
        int Length of BigDecimal substring parsed from String

        public static int intFromString(String string,

        Takes a string and pulls out a substring representing an int starting at designated index until hits next non-Digit, or non-negative sign char. Converts the substring to an int Examples: intFromString("abs423", 3) = 423; intFromString("abs423", 4) = 23;
